<FTL>
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_ZOLTAN_SHIELD_EXTRACTOR">
    <title>RK Shield (1)</title>
    <desc>This RadiKal Punk augment provides 1 layer of supershields, for when you really just want to avoid immediate mind control, teleport or hacking issues.</desc>
    <cost>20</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- see 'textless events' in modding tips folder -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_COMBAT_OFFENSE_DISABLER">
    <title>Offense Disabler</title>
    <desc>This RadiKal Punk combat augment disables enemy offensive systems (Weapons, Drone Control, Hacking, Mind Control, Teleporter, and one Artillery) for 5 seconds. The effect then weakens progressively until it's gone at 18 seconds (you will be warned).
		Perfect against aggressive enemies! [Uses 3| and 3 reactor power. Emergency Generator can apply.]</desc>
    <cost>75</cost>
    <rarity>4</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!--
Jump event augment! Code is still in combat augment xml for technical reasons though.
Disabled because too damn CLUNKY since it forces player to confirm every jump, even without having the augment...
Some add-on that came out in the meantime has done a better implementation of this, check it out.

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_JUMP_DECOY">
    <title>Jump Decoy</title>
    <desc>When you escape a fight by performing an FTL jump, this sends a fake jump signature to a different destination. Your enemy has a 25% chance to transmit this misleading intel, delaying the rebel fleet for 1 turn.</desc>
    <cost>30</cost>
    <rarity>1</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

REWORKED JumpDecoy -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_HACK_FLEET">
    <title>Enigmashin</title>
    <desc>This RadiKal Punk combat augment needs a level 2 Hacking system on your ship. 
	Attempts to send deepfake intel to the rebels through an enemy's comms for credibility.
	On average, success delays the fleet 75% of the time and failure accelerates it 10% of the time. If you deal more than 2 hull damage during the process, it stops. [Reduces player Hacking power by 2 for 17s, uses 2|]</desc>
    <cost>35</cost>
    <rarity>3</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_SUPER_DEFENDERS">
    <title>Defense Kits</title>
    <desc>This RadiKal Punk augment makes your crew better at survival on your ship.
	x0.75 damage taken, x1.3 repair speed, x1.3 movement speed, and a 4 HP/second heal while idle (not even manning).</desc>
    <cost>90</cost>
    <rarity>4</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<!-- Daft Punk H B F S reference -->
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_OWN_HARMONY_ON">
    <title>Punk Harmony</title>
    <desc>Some daft RadiKal Punks made their own Harmony. Controls your Engis on your ship, giving them immunity to (further) mind control and +40% damage and stun resistance. Powered levels in Hacking or Mind Control add 5/10/20/40/80/160% combat damage, and repair and movement speed.
	
	In short, makes them harder, better, faster, stronger, and automated.
	
	Can be toggled off anytime.</desc>
    <cost>70</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_OWN_HARMONY_OFF">
    <title>Punk Harmony (OFF)</title>
    <desc>Some daft RadiKal Punks made their own Harmony. Controls your Engis on your ship, giving them immunity to (further) mind control and +40% damage and stun resistance. Powered levels in Hacking or Mind Control add 5/10/20/40/80/160% combat damage, and repair and movement speed.
	
	In short, makes them harder, better, faster, stronger, and automated.
	
	Can be toggled on anytime.</desc>
    <cost>70</cost>
    <rarity>0</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_DEFENSE_REMOVER">
    <title>Vulnerabilizer</title>
    <desc>This powerful RadiKal Punk combat augment slowly weakens the enemy's defenses. Every 3 to 7 seconds (at random), limits enemy Shields and Engines by 1 power. This effect stacks. All effects end after a duration based on how many | you spent.[Uses 3 reactor power. Emergency Generator can apply.]</desc>
    <cost>100</cost>
    <rarity>5</rarity>
    <stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
</FTL>

