<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_COMBAT_SCORCH_ENEMY">
	<title>Plasma Teleporter</title>
	<desc>This combat augment from the RadiKal Scorch can set the enemy ship on fire at start of combat, outright winning some fights.
		Needs a fire source: RK firestarting equipment, Gouls, Lost Suns, Shells, Zoltans, or 3}.
		[Uses 1{, ignites your O2 system.]

	COMBO: Charged Belts / Martyr Vests make all crew fire sources.
	COMBO: any Scorched Earth can provide the fire for free.</desc>
	<cost>75</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_ENEMIES_CAN_BURN">
	<title>Flammabilizer-Immune</title>
	<desc>This RadiKal Scorch augment removes the fire immunity and resistance of enemies by limiting their total fire resistance, based on the energy in your O2 system (90/75/55/30 resistance at 0/1/2/3 power respectively).
	Also makes enemies move 12% slower in fire (up to 50% with 3 power in O2).
	Works on both ships.

	Can be toggled to make non-fireproof enemies take more fire damage instead.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_ENEMIES_BURN_MORE">
	<title>Flammabilizer-Damage</title>
	<desc>This RadiKal Scorch augment makes non-fireproof enemies take 50% more fire damage (scaling up to 250% with 4 energy in O2).
	Also makes enemies move 12% slower in fire (up to 50% with 3 power in O2).
	Works on both ships.
	
	Can be toggled to make fireproof and fire-resistant enemies vulnerable to fire instead.</desc>
	<cost>100</cost>
	<rarity>5</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>

<augBlueprint name="DJMOD_OXYGENIZER">
	<title>Oxygenizer</title>
	<desc>This RadiKal Scorch combat augment can basically shoot out giant canisters of ultracompressed O2 to fill the void of space when a fight starts.
	Puts both ship in an atmosphere, making breaches and open vents fill oxygen instead of depleting it. Shenanigans ensue. [Uses 2}]</desc>
	<cost>40</cost>
	<rarity>4</rarity>
	<stackable>false</stackable>
</augBlueprint>
</FTL>


